parameters.name: AccelerateIpAddress
parameters.description: The accelerated IP address of the basic GA instance.

parameters.name: AccelerateIpId
parameters.description: The ID of the accelerated IP address of the basic GA instance.

parameters.name: ClientToken
parameters.description:
The client token that is used to ensure the idempotence of the request.

You can use the client to generate the value, but you must make sure that it is unique among different requests. The client token can contain only ASCII characters.

>  If you do not set this parameter, **ClientToken** is set to the value of **RequestId**. The value of **RequestId** for each API request may be different.

parameters.name: IpSetId
parameters.description: The ID of the acceleration region.

parameters.name: MaxResults
parameters.description: The number of entries to return on each page. Valid values: **1** to **50**. Default value: **10**.

parameters.name: NextToken
parameters.description:
The token that determines the start point of the query. Valid values:

*   If this is your first query and no next queries are to be sent, ignore this parameter.
*   If a subsequent query is to be sent, set the parameter to the value of NextToken that is returned from the last call.

parameters.name: RegionId
parameters.description: The ID of the region where the GA instance is deployed. Set the value to **cn-hangzhou**.
